 eclipse data returns a\ntemperature of $2550_{-250}^{+150}$ K and a pressure of\n$10^{-1.5_{-0.6}^{+0.7}}$ bar at the lower layer of the temperature inversion.\nThe detection of such a strong temperature inversion is consistent with\ntheoretical simulations that predict an inversion layer on the dayside of UHJs.\nThe joint retrieval of the CARMENES and TESS data demonstrates the power of\ncombing high-resolution emission spectroscopy with secondary eclipse photometry\nin characterizing atmospheric temperature structures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Jan 2022 16:12:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
